snippet.title: Margot Robbie: Plastic Surgery, Skin & Her Real Age
snippet.description:
Today I will be talking about the glamorous Margot Robbie, Australian actress and film producer. I will explore the truth about Margot Robbie’s age, and how she attained her beautiful youthful look. Possible cosmetic procedures such as a nose job, Botox brow-lifts, dermal fillers and a renowned skincare routine. (her favorite skincare products are linked down below)#MargotRobbie #Skincare #Plasticsurgery

About Margot Robbie
Margot has had a globally successful career in acting. Her acting career started when she was young and had graduated from Somerset College. Soon after graduation, she took some small roles, until she landed a regular part on the Australian soap opera show “Neighbors”. Soon after leaving the show, she moved to the USA and starred in a Rom-Com called “About time”, giving her enough recognition to get her breakout roles in the Worldwide success, Wolf Of wall street ( which grossed 392 million dollars worldwide), where she played the wife of the ruthless Stock trader, Jordan Belfort, played by Leonardo DiCaprio. Her next largest role was in the Super-villain movie “ S Squad” (which took the box office by storm with 746.8 million dollars in revenue), playing Harley Quinn, a character that is now a fan favorite. She has starred in many works, but those are the most commonly known. Over her acting career, she has won many awards, and has been one of the highest paid actresses in recent times with a reported annual income of around $23.5 million.

Her acting success led to her starting a business alongside her husband Tom Ackerley. Together they started a Film Production Company called “LuckyChap Entertainment”. Beyond  film producing, she has also been the brand ambassador for many marketing campaigns, most notable are Fashion brand Calvin Klein, luxury fashion brand Chanel, and Chanel Fragrance lines.  She also did some work for some Nissan car commercials. For now she is rumored to soon be starring in a live action Barbie movie, and an upcoming Pirates of the Caribbean reboot.

As far as her beauty goes, is it makeup, dieting, Genetics, or cosmetic procedures that keeps her looking young & radiant? 
Margot often tells people to make sure to add powerful sunscreen into their skincare routine to keep their skin looking flawless. Her favorite sunscreen is Neutrogena SPF 100+ which she wears whenever makeup like tinted foundation with SPF 30 protection cannot be used.

Margot Robbie’s Skincare routine:


1.Her makeup remover is Johnson’s Face care Makeup wipes: https://go.magik.ly/ml/ypov/

2.Her preferred skin cleanser is Lancer The Method: Cleanse https://go.magik.ly/ml/ypor/

3.She also uses an exfoliator, Peter Thomas Roth Max complexion correction Pads: https://go.magik.ly/ml/ypop/

4. To combat dry skin, she uses face mists:Caudalie Beauty Elixr https://go.magik.ly/ml/ypp0/ and Aesop Immediate moisture Hydrosol https://go.magik.ly/ml/ypp2/

5. For eye cream & moisturizer she uses La Praire Skin Caviar Luxe Eye Cream right after a shower to keep in skin moisture https://go.magik.ly/ml/ypp6/

7. Margot Robbie always has Sunscreen, when she isn't wearing her favorite Neutrogena 100spf suncreen:https://go.magik.ly/ml/yppu/, to protect her face, she uses tinted foundation/sunscreen spf https://go.magik.ly/ml/yppa/


8. For her lips, Margot wears two different lip balms, Burt’s Bees Tinted lip balm for some color and moisture: https://go.magik.ly/ml/yppb/ and https://go.magik.ly/ml/yppc/ , A Fresh sugar Tinted Lip Treatment with spf 15. Margot likes to avoid sun damage on her skin.

9. The last product she uses is a very expensive Bio Cellulose Facial Mask: https://go.magik.ly/ml/yppd/

Dermatologist is: Dr. Harold Lancer

(Some of these links are affiliate links to Ulta Beauty, Sephora, Nordstrom and other retailers, when you make a purchase it helps the channel)
